The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Tea output jumps 17% in February
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Tea output jumps 17% in February
          A STAFF REPORTER                                            
	Calcutta, April 8: Tea output rose 17 per cent to 17.97 million kg in February against 15.2 million kg a year ago, according to the Tea Board of India.        
	The volume and value of exports as well as prices increased during the month. Exports slightly increased to 12.24 million kg in February against 12.15 million kg in the same month last year.        
	Production growth, however, has not been uniform, with the northern regions  Assam Valley, Cachar, Darjeeling, Dooars and Terai  witnessing falling trends over last year. Production spurts have been reported from the southern regions of Tamil Nadu, Karnataka and Kerala.        
	Output in January and February increased 23 per cent to 45.1 million kg.        
	During February, production in north India fell almost half to 1.5 million kg from three million kg in the previous year, while south India saw an increase of 4.2 million kg to 16.4 million kg.         
	During the 11-month period of 2009-10 ended February, production in north India fell 2.9 million kg to 10.2 million kg, while it rose 11.1 million kg to nearly 35 million kg in south India.        
	According to the United Planters Association of Southern India, the main reason for the growth in output in the south during January-February was the absence of frost in winter and fairly good showers during December.         
	Cumulative production in the April-February period of 2009-10 rose over 22 per cent at 45 million kg against 36.8 million kg in the year-ago period.         
	Price trend        
	In February, average price moved up about 6 per cent to Rs 130.75 per kg, while it increased 10.45 per cent to Rs 137.41 a kg in the April-February period of 2009-10, the Tea Board data said.        
	In value terms, exports rose about 7 per cent to Rs 160.06 crore in February, while it rose 14.13 per cent in the April-February period to Rs 2,504.70 crore from the corresponding period of the previous fiscal.                                                                                                                                             
